I'm John Cavanaugh,
and I manage the group

00:00:15.186 --> 00:00:17.576 A:middle
that creates the
documentation for all

00:00:17.576 --> 00:00:19.606 A:middle
of Apple's consumer
and Pro products.

00:00:20.156 --> 00:00:21.296 A:middle
And here's some of what we do.

00:00:22.536 --> 00:00:29.236 A:middle
Print pieces that come in
the box, iBooks and PDFs,

00:00:29.406 --> 00:00:32.706 A:middle
help topics that appear
in the OS X Help Viewer.

00:00:33.436 --> 00:00:36.816 A:middle
We have some highly
contextual In-App solutions

00:00:37.726 --> 00:00:41.416 A:middle
and deliverables on the web
like these iOS user guides

00:00:42.536 --> 00:00:45.346 A:middle
or this What's New
Experience you may have seen

00:00:45.586 --> 00:00:47.966 A:middle
in OS X Mavericks.

00:00:47.966 --> 00:00:53.476 A:middle
Now, creating great customer
documentation isn't always seen

00:00:53.476 --> 00:00:56.986 A:middle
as one of the most exciting
parts of software development -

00:00:57.246 --> 00:00:59.616 A:middle
I realize that as the
documentation guy.


