00:46:59.246 --> 00:47:01.296 A:middle
And with games, "Leo's Fortune."

00:47:01.426 --> 00:47:03.416 A:middle
That chalk drawing is
giving you that little hint.

00:47:04.586 --> 00:47:06.796 A:middle
And they don't just do this
in the tutorial level -

00:47:06.796 --> 00:47:10.046 A:middle
it's throughout the game.

00:47:10.236 --> 00:47:13.496 A:middle
In fact, showing information
inline is often a great

00:47:13.496 --> 00:47:15.656 A:middle
alternative to onboarding
altogether.

00:47:16.416 --> 00:47:17.986 A:middle
You don't have to tell
everything up front.

00:47:18.576 --> 00:47:22.496 A:middle
Just put the extra information
inline so it's there right

00:47:22.496 --> 00:47:24.606 A:middle
in that moment that
people need it.

00:47:26.846 --> 00:47:29.836 A:middle
Now, another great approach
is to watch for indications

00:47:29.836 --> 00:47:31.866 A:middle
that people are stuck.

00:47:32.856 --> 00:47:35.436 A:middle
Now, when it comes to games,
though, you have to be wary

00:47:35.436 --> 00:47:37.796 A:middle
about over-helping people
because it's a game,

00:47:38.526 --> 00:47:41.126 A:middle
nobody enjoys having the
puzzle solved for them.

00:47:41.236 --> 00:47:42.076 A:middle
That's not fun.

00:47:42.886 --> 00:47:45.806 A:middle
You want to give people a
chance to play all on their own

00:47:45.876 --> 00:47:47.906 A:middle
and then watch for clues
they might be stuck.

00:47:47.906 --> 00:47:52.636 A:middle
And that's when you
offer the help.

00:47:52.816 --> 00:47:56.136 A:middle
With "Leo's Fortune," if you
try a number of times to get

00:47:56.136 --> 00:47:58.716 A:middle
over this very basic obstacle
and you don't make it,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:48:00.016 --> 00:48:02.046 A:middle
they give you the option
of onscreen controls.

00:48:02.886 --> 00:48:05.076 A:middle
Again, they only
do this if it looks

00:48:05.076 --> 00:48:07.666 A:middle
like you're struggling
with that first jump.

00:48:09.116 --> 00:48:11.166 A:middle
"The Room Two" also
has a great approach.

00:48:11.166 --> 00:48:15.716 A:middle
Now, if you haven't played it,
it's a mystery puzzler game.

00:48:16.326 --> 00:48:18.816 A:middle
You're stuck in this room and
you follow clue, after clue,

00:48:18.816 --> 00:48:20.616 A:middle
after clue to make your escape.

00:48:21.266 --> 00:48:23.386 A:middle
Now, if you've been
struggling for a long time,

00:48:24.196 --> 00:48:26.556 A:middle
and you still didn't manage
to accomplish the next thing,

00:48:27.426 --> 00:48:29.196 A:middle
they give you this
question mark button.

00:48:29.736 --> 00:48:35.986 A:middle
And this is great because it's
giving you the option of a hint.

00:48:36.166 --> 00:48:37.676 A:middle
Because it's true,
I might be stuck,

00:48:38.876 --> 00:48:40.606 A:middle
or I may have been distracted.

00:48:41.856 --> 00:48:44.626 A:middle
My dog may have started barking,
or someone needed something

00:48:44.626 --> 00:48:45.806 A:middle
and walked into the room.

00:48:46.386 --> 00:48:49.186 A:middle
So that's really good because
they're not solving the puzzle

00:48:49.256 --> 00:48:50.406 A:middle
for me.

00:48:51.536 --> 00:48:55.316 A:middle
However, if I am really
stuck and I'm at the point

00:48:55.316 --> 00:48:57.556 A:middle
of walking away, it's
enough to keep me engaged,

00:48:57.556 --> 00:48:58.716 A:middle
to keep me moving forward.

00:48:59.276 --> 00:49:03.126 A:middle
And instead of giving away the
answers, they give you clues


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:48:59.276 --> 00:49:03.126 A:middle
And instead of giving away the
answers, they give you clues

00:49:03.126 --> 00:49:04.996 A:middle
so you don't have
to feel guilty.

00:49:04.996 --> 00:49:06.516 A:middle
It doesn't have to
feel like cheating.

00:49:06.596 --> 00:49:08.526 A:middle
You don't have to feel
bad about it, right?

00:49:08.526 --> 00:49:11.936 A:middle
And this doesn't devalue
the achievements of people

00:49:11.936 --> 00:49:12.956 A:middle
who didn't use the clues.

00:49:13.496 --> 00:49:14.676 A:middle
We're all going to
get to the end.

00:49:15.826 --> 00:49:17.836 A:middle
Some of us are going
to get there faster,

00:49:18.186 --> 00:49:19.496 A:middle
but this works out really well.

00:49:19.496 --> 00:49:22.066 A:middle
Everyone can feel really good
when they finish the game.

00:49:22.696 --> 00:49:26.706 A:middle
And these kind of hints can
be helpful with apps too.

