00:50:16.466 --> 00:50:19.296 A:middle
and that glow calls
attention to itself.

00:50:20.436 --> 00:50:22.756 A:middle
They're using animation
to attract your attention.

00:50:22.756 --> 00:50:25.376 A:middle
And that's really elegant

00:50:25.496 --> 00:50:28.526 A:middle
because if you double-tap
a star thinking oh,

00:50:28.526 --> 00:50:31.406 A:middle
maybe I didn't tap hard enough
or maybe I need to tap twice,

00:50:31.866 --> 00:50:35.036 A:middle
they pulse every time you
tap, to get your attention.

00:50:35.796 --> 00:50:39.586 A:middle
So they're keeping an eye
out for you that you're stuck

00:50:39.836 --> 00:50:41.866 A:middle
and trying to pull you
in the right direction,

00:50:42.236 --> 00:50:45.546 A:middle
get you back on track.

00:50:45.546 --> 00:50:48.046 A:middle
And all of these tips that
I've shown you are really just

00:50:48.046 --> 00:50:50.006 A:middle
about anticipating
people's needs.

00:50:50.786 --> 00:50:53.546 A:middle
Telling people what they
need to know in the moment

00:50:53.546 --> 00:50:55.376 A:middle
that they need to know it.

00:50:55.516 --> 00:50:59.206 A:middle
Think about the restaurant again
that I talked about earlier.

00:50:59.966 --> 00:51:02.106 A:middle
You don't want to see the
dessert menu before you've been


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:50:59.966 --> 00:51:02.106 A:middle
You don't want to see the
dessert menu before you've been

00:51:02.166 --> 00:51:04.856 A:middle
seated or while you're
eating your appetizer.

00:51:05.136 --> 00:51:06.596 A:middle
You want it when you
finish your meal.

00:51:07.256 --> 00:51:10.696 A:middle
And when you have good
service at a restaurant,

00:51:10.696 --> 00:51:13.126 A:middle
it means the wait staff is
there when you need them,

00:51:13.376 --> 00:51:14.836 A:middle
and they're not there
when you don't.

00:51:16.166 --> 00:51:18.816 A:middle
And that's exactly the
approach you want to take

00:51:18.816 --> 00:51:20.816 A:middle
if you've got help inside
of your application.

00:51:22.436 --> 00:51:24.726 A:middle
And "Secret" is really
one of the best examples

00:51:24.726 --> 00:51:26.016 A:middle
that I've seen out there.

00:51:26.596 --> 00:51:28.606 A:middle
It's an anonymous
social networking app.

00:51:28.916 --> 00:51:31.616 A:middle
So what this means is that you
see posts from your friends,

00:51:31.616 --> 00:51:33.996 A:middle
but you don't know who they are
because everything is anonymous.

00:51:34.806 --> 00:51:37.406 A:middle
That's a really interesting
way to interact with people.

00:51:38.306 --> 00:51:41.896 A:middle
Now, the first time your feed
loads, they're explaining

00:51:41.896 --> 00:51:43.916 A:middle
in a moment exactly
the information

00:51:43.916 --> 00:51:44.656 A:middle
that you need to know.

00:51:46.076 --> 00:51:48.406 A:middle
So here, I'm scrolling
through my feed,

00:51:48.406 --> 00:51:50.736 A:middle
and I don't know
anyone in the UK.

00:51:50.736 --> 00:51:53.436 A:middle
Oh, it's traveled
across friends.

00:51:54.336 --> 00:51:56.426 A:middle
Speaking of friends,
where are my friends?

00:51:57.916 --> 00:52:00.356 A:middle
Oh, I didn't have
my phone number yet.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:51:57.916 --> 00:52:00.356 A:middle
Oh, I didn't have
my phone number yet.

00:52:00.946 --> 00:52:04.376 A:middle
Shoot. And what's the
star mean, I wonder?

00:52:05.086 --> 00:52:06.126 A:middle
It's a popular one.

00:52:06.826 --> 00:52:08.066 A:middle
And when you go to Comments,

00:52:09.776 --> 00:52:12.246 A:middle
they explain why there
