00:52:12.806 --> 00:52:15.536 A:middle
They're just letting you know
about commenting because that's

00:52:15.536 --> 00:52:16.736 A:middle
where you are in the app.

00:52:17.506 --> 00:52:19.206 A:middle
They're not telling
you about navigation

00:52:19.206 --> 00:52:21.206 A:middle
or what does the star mean
and things like that -

00:52:21.206 --> 00:52:22.676 A:middle
they're focused on commenting.

00:52:23.876 --> 00:52:25.906 A:middle
And it's worth noting that
they're just giving one piece

00:52:25.906 --> 00:52:29.586 A:middle
of information at
a time as well.

00:52:29.706 --> 00:52:31.496 A:middle
And if you're the
first to comment,

00:52:31.766 --> 00:52:35.666 A:middle
they've populated their
empty view with information.

00:52:36.036 --> 00:52:37.666 A:middle
You know that comments
are going to be there.

00:52:38.256 --> 00:52:40.546 A:middle
This little gentle push
should be the first one,

00:52:41.596 --> 00:52:45.316 A:middle
and I just love that the
placeholder text encourages you

00:52:45.316 --> 00:52:46.816 A:middle
to say something kind.

00:52:47.306 --> 00:52:48.006 A:middle
It's great.

00:52:48.656 --> 00:52:52.886 A:middle
So think about what people need
to know based on where they are

00:52:52.886 --> 00:52:56.276 A:middle
in your app or game, how
long they've been using it,

00:52:56.276 --> 00:52:58.786 A:middle
and anticipating people's
needs is just another way

00:52:58.786 --> 00:53:00.416 A:middle
that you're going to
be able to provide help


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:52:58.786 --> 00:53:00.416 A:middle
that you're going to
be able to provide help

00:53:00.706 --> 00:53:02.376 A:middle
without it feeling like help.

00:53:03.096 --> 00:53:08.756 A:middle
And be sure to take the
opportunity to inspire people

00:53:09.066 --> 00:53:11.306 A:middle
like "Secret" did with
"say something kind."

00:53:11.956 --> 00:53:17.246 A:middle
Now, a lot of people use Siri
to set reminders or send text

00:53:17.246 --> 00:53:20.636 A:middle
or check sports scores,
things like that, but remember

00:53:20.636 --> 00:53:22.696 A:middle
when you found out that
Siri would answer questions

00:53:22.696 --> 00:53:24.066 A:middle
like this?

00:53:24.616 --> 00:53:27.736 A:middle
I mean, all of a sudden, this
convenience feature is a source

00:53:27.736 --> 00:53:29.226 A:middle
of entertainment as well.

00:53:30.076 --> 00:53:34.606 A:middle
It's unexpected and fun, and
now Siri is more valuable to me

00:53:35.356 --> 00:53:37.326 A:middle
because she's not just
a utility anymore.

00:53:37.326 --> 00:53:38.286 A:middle
She's comedy.

00:53:38.736 --> 00:53:39.786 A:middle
She's flattery.

00:53:40.126 --> 00:53:40.836 A:middle
It's great.

00:53:42.296 --> 00:53:45.346 A:middle
People might come to your app
with a certain expectation

00:53:46.326 --> 00:53:49.356 A:middle
about getting one thing
done, but when they discover

00:53:49.356 --> 00:53:51.126 A:middle
that your app can
do more for them,

00:53:51.356 --> 00:53:53.926 A:middle
well then the app becomes
even more valuable.

00:53:55.036 --> 00:53:57.806 A:middle
It's going to feel
like a bonus prize.

00:53:59.416 --> 00:54:02.416 A:middle
And that's why with Siri, we
give you a lot of suggestions


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:53:59.416 --> 00:54:02.416 A:middle
And that's why with Siri, we
give you a lot of suggestions

00:54:02.416 --> 00:54:03.956 A:middle
of things that you can ask her.

00:54:04.056 --> 00:54:06.546 A:middle
You just tap that question
mark button and you're going

00:54:06.546 --> 00:54:09.456 A:middle
to get a long list of things
that you can ask Siri.

00:54:10.246 --> 00:54:13.756 A:middle
And you may have known that you
can use Siri to initiate calls

00:54:13.756 --> 00:54:17.056 A:middle
or have her make an
appointment on your calendar,

00:54:17.056 --> 00:54:20.216 A:middle
but did you know that she also
will book restaurants for you

00:54:20.776 --> 00:54:22.086 A:middle
or tell you movie times?

00:54:22.336 --> 00:54:25.036 A:middle
I mean, this list goes
on, and on and on.

00:54:27.076 --> 00:54:29.376 A:middle
"Path" does it with some
of their onboarding.

00:54:29.836 --> 00:54:32.956 A:middle
And they're a private social
network, so they really need you

00:54:32.956 --> 00:54:35.086 A:middle
to register because
everything is oriented

00:54:35.086 --> 00:54:36.436 A:middle
around your personal
information.

00:54:37.436 --> 00:54:40.736 A:middle
But before registering, they're
giving you a series of screens

00:54:40.736 --> 00:54:44.176 A:middle
that covers both the
features of the apps

00:54:44.316 --> 00:54:46.886 A:middle
but also how you might
want to use them.

00:54:48.286 --> 00:54:50.616 A:middle
A lot of people go to "Path"
thinking they're going to use it

00:54:50.616 --> 00:54:52.456 A:middle
for work, but now, they're
going to be thinking

00:54:52.456 --> 00:54:55.226 A:middle
about how they can use it
in their personal life, too.

00:54:57.516 --> 00:55:01.096 A:middle
Or with Pinterest, they've
got a similar approach.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:54:57.516 --> 00:55:01.096 A:middle
Or with Pinterest, they've
got a similar approach.

00:55:01.696 --> 00:55:03.236 A:middle
I mean, maybe you
came to Pinterest

00:55:03.236 --> 00:55:06.296 A:middle
because you were interested
in nail art or wanting recipes

00:55:06.296 --> 00:55:08.706 A:middle
for a dinner party, but
now you're also thinking

00:55:08.706 --> 00:55:09.806 A:middle
about gardening.

00:55:10.806 --> 00:55:11.716 A:middle
And then you're thinking

00:55:11.716 --> 00:55:13.846 A:middle
about what else Pinterest
can be used for.

00:55:14.496 --> 00:55:19.106 A:middle
So step away from that
traditional idea of help,

00:55:19.586 --> 00:55:22.006 A:middle
reference manuals, and think

00:55:22.006 --> 00:55:24.366 A:middle
about how you can
anticipate people's needs.

00:55:25.506 --> 00:55:27.726 A:middle
Putting instructions
in empty containers

00:55:27.726 --> 00:55:30.186 A:middle
and showing supporting
information inline,

00:55:30.706 --> 00:55:33.446 A:middle
it's about telling people what
they need to know in that moment

00:55:33.966 --> 00:55:37.036 A:middle
that they need to know it
- like the perfect service

00:55:37.096 --> 00:55:39.976 A:middle
in a restaurant, there
when you need them

00:55:39.976 --> 00:55:42.956 A:middle
and invisible when you don't.

00:55:43.066 --> 00:55:45.006 A:middle
When you're doing all
of that, don't forget

00:55:45.036 --> 00:55:47.166 A:middle
to take the opportunity
to inspire people,

00:55:47.166 --> 00:55:49.056 A:middle
because that increased
knowledge,

